title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.4 Maternal, Neonatal, and Child Health (MNCH)

description.narrative: Output 1.4: Government and partner institutions have enhanced capacity and commitment to deliver quality basic and comprehensive MNCH services including PPTCT at scale., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Care And Treatment Of Children Affected By Hiv And Aids, Child Health, Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Health Systems Strengthening, Hiv Prevention, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Micronutrients, Pmtct And Infant Male Circumcision, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: Women and children have more equitable access to evidence-based health, nutrition, Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) and HIV services and adopt appropriate care practices from pregnancy to adolescence.
